Package game

package game
This package contains classes used for implementation of different game modes (Simulation and Debug) and variants (DoubleBonus 10/7). The interfaces and abstract classes in this package allow for implementation of new game modes and poker variants.
Author:
Diogo Martins, Jose Brito, Xavier Fernandes
  • Class
    Description
    AbstractDebug
    Abstract class that extends the AbstractMode class.
    AbstractDoubleBonus
    Abstract class that extends the AbstractVariant class.
    AbstractMode
    Abstract class that implements the IMode interface.
    AbstractSimulation
    Abstract class that extends the AbstractMode class.
    AbstractVariant
    Abstract class that implements the IVvariant interface.
    Debug
    Debugging class that extends the AbstractDebug class.
    DoubleBonus107
    Class that extends the AbstractDoubleBonus class.
    IMode
    Game mode interface that specifies a required method for a game mode implementation.
    IVariant
    Interface that specifies the required methods for variants of poker.
    Player
    Player class, which includes the number of credits and the player's hand.
    Simulation
    Simulation class which extends the AbstractSimulation class.
